3 NEW SECTION. SECTION 5. LONG-TERM SUSTAINABILITY OF HB 872 STUDY -- COMMITTEE. (1) DURING
4 THE INTERIM FOLLOWING THE 69TH LEGISLATIVE SESSION, THERE IS A HOUSE BILL NO. 872 LONG-TERM SUSTAINABILITY
5 COMMITTEE TO ANALYZE AND PROPOSE MECHANISMS TO PROVIDE SUSTAINABLE FUNDING FOR LONG-TERM OBJECTIVES
6 OF HOUSE BILL NO. 872 TO THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH AND TO THE LEGISLATIVE FINANCE COMMITTEE IN PREPARATION
7 FOR THE 70TH LEGISLATIVE SESSION.
8 (2) THE COMMITTEE CONSISTS OF THE FOLLOWING MEMBERS:
9 (A) THE CHAIR OF THE HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES APPROPRIATIONS JOINT SUBCOMMITTEE;
10 (B) TWO FOUR MEMBERS OF THE HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES APPROPRIATIONS JOINT SUBCOMMITTEE,
11 WITH ONE APPOINTED BY THE SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE, AND ONE APPOINTED BY THE MINORITY LEADER OF THE HOUSE,
12 ONE APPOINTED BY THE PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE, AND ONE APPOINTED BY THE MINORITY LEADER OF THE SENATE, in
13 CONSULTATION WITH THE CHAIR OF THE HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES APPROPRIATIONS JOINT SUBCOMMITTEE;
14 (C) THE DIRECTOR OF THE DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, OR THE DIRECTOR'S
15 DESIGNEE;
16 (D) THE MEDICAID BUREAU CHIEF; AND
17 (E) THE BUDGET DIRECTOR OR THE DIRECTOR'S DESIGNEE.
18 (3) THE DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES SHALL STAFF THE COMMITTEE AND PAY
19 FOR THE OPERATIONAL COSTS OF THE COMMITTEE.
20 (4) THE OFFICE OF BUDGET AND PROGRAM PLANNING AND THE LEGISLATIVE FISCAL DIVISION SHALL
21 PROVIDE RESEARCH AND ANALYSIS AT THE REQUEST OF THE COMMITTEE.
22 (5) THE COMMITTEE SHALL ELECT A PRESIDING OFFICER FROM ONE OF THE MEMBERS WHO IS A
23 LEGISLATOR AND ELECT A VICE PRESIDING OFFICER.
24 (6) STARTING JUNE 1, 2025, THE COMMITTEE SHALL MEET EVERY 2 MONTHS AND MAY MEET REMOTELY.
25 (7) THE COMMITTEE SHALL RESERVE TIME AT EACH COMMITTEE MEETING FOR PUBLIC COMMENT. PUBLIC
26 PARTICIPATION IS ENCOURAGED.
